      "text": "ClearTax buys content aggregation app TOOTL T+ T- Archit Gupta, CEO, ClearTax Bengaluru, April 11 \nClearTax, a fintech company that offers intelligent software solutions for compliance with direct and indirect taxes, has acquired Greeblu Enterprises, an app-based start-up. \nTOOTL, an infotainment app developed by Greeblu, is a pocket-buddy that understands the reader’s preferences and accordingly personalises relevant content the user would want to explore further. ClearTax is set to use this technology to curate personalised tax, finance and compliance related content on its website. \n“This algorithm has been a great value add to our existing systems. In the tax and finance sphere, ClearTax is known for its exhaustive content. We will utilise the TOOTL technology to enhance customer engagement and provide tailored content based on income, financial goals, age and other parameters. This would help our customers make informed financial decisions, taking us a step closer to our mission of simplifying finance for Indians,” said Archit Gupta, founder and CEO, ClearTax. \nThe company has been on the lookout for innovative ways to improve user experience and acquiring TOOTL was one such effort. \nSince 2011, ClearTax has been rapidly branching out into multiple domains and offers products and services such as a mutual fund investment portal, GST software, EWayBill generator, DSC utility and business compliance services, while maintaining market dominance in tax filing services. Published on",
