      "title": "Students should build the four positive C’s- Character, Calibre, Capacity and Conduct, Say Venkaiah Naidu",
      "text": "GREATER NOIDA: BIMTECH’S Convocation Day was celebrated with much pomp and show on 11 th April, 2018 with 423 students being awarded their postgraduate degrees. The students belonged to different streams which included post graduate diploma- General/ Insurance/Retail management and International business. The function was held with a huge gathering in India Exposition Mart, Greater Noida.\nAs an eminent political figure, Vice President – Venkaiah Naidu gained prominence as a brilliant orator, who vigorously championed the cause of the farmers and the development of backward areas. Previously, he served as the Minister of Housing and Urban Poverty Alleviation, Urban Development and Information and Broadcasting in Modi’s Cabinet.\nAccording to Venkaiah Naidu, “Twenty first century India has got some extraordinary talent which the youth must upgrade from time to time so that they grab opportunities that will help them to excel in the corporate world. He laid emphasis on the fact that students should build the four positive C’s- Character, Calibre, Capacity and Conduct.” He further coined words such as “Reform, Perform, and Transform” to encourage the students to become worthy citizens of the country.\nThe students of batch 2016-18 felt really delighted and privileged on being given their diplomas by the Vice President himself. And the message that the honourable vice president gave to the passing batch was that education should not be for commission instead it should instil values. Also he said that talented youth should assume the role of being job creators instead of being job seekers. This process might give temporary pain but will deliver long term gains. He quoted former president of India Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam and said “That one should aim high and work hard for it”.\nLastly he appreciated BIMTECH for its various endeavours and said that knowledge has no frontiers and one must care for the ones close to us and specially work for the betterment of the society.\nDr. H. Chaturvedi, Director, BIMTECH presented the annual report and gave his blessings to the students.\nIt was a day of mixed emotions for all the students who were passing out .On one hand they were elated on getting their diplomas and posed happily with their batch mates in their full black convocation attire which had them wearing their academic caps and black robes, whereas on the other hand they were emotional about going away from a place in which they had strings of memories attached and which had taught them a lot.\nThe following students were felicitated on the occasion for excellence in academic and extracurricular activities:\nGold Medal Awarded to Aditya Vardhan for Securing Overall First Position In PGDM Gold Medal Awarded to Shallika Singh for Securing Overall First Position In PGDM (IB) Gold Medal Awarded to Yashaswi Agrawal for Securing Overall First Position In PGDM (IBM) Gold Medal Awarded to Mr. Praveen Kumar A for Securing Overall First Position In PGDM (RM) Special Medal Awarded to Sonali Gupta For Securing First Position In The ‘Marketing’ Specialization Stream In PGDM Special Medal Awarded to Roncy Sara Thomas for Securing First Position In The ‘Operations’ Specialization Stream In PGDM Special Medal Awarded to Mr. Aditya Vardhan for Securing First Position In The ‘Finance’ Specialization Stream In PGDM Special Medal Awarded to Ms. Divya Negi for Securing First Position In The ‘Human Resource’ Specialization Stream In PGDM Dr. C.B.Gupta Memorial Medal – 2018, For All-Round Best Performance Among Male Students, Awarded To Mr. Praveen Kumar A Smt.Yashoda Jaju Memorial Medal – 2018, For All-Round Best Performance Among Female Students, Awarded To Shallika Singh Smt. Madhuri J Sheth Award For Best Academic Performance, Among Female Students of PGDM, Awarded To Tanvi Jain Smt. Madhuri J Sheth Award For Best Academic Performance, Among Female Students of PGDM (International Business), Awarded To Ms. Shallika Singh Sarla Devi Birla Award for best Best Chiraiya (life skills education programme of Bimtech) to Sujata Gautam Jagdish N Sheth award for Best Thesis to Dr. Amarendra Pande and Dr. Himanshu Gupta The post Students should build the four positive C’s- Character, Calibre, Capacity and Conduct, Say Venkaiah Naidu appeared first on India's Largest CSR Network .\n",
